    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-data-processing/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MS data were converted from .RAW (Thermo) standard data format to .mzXML format using the MSConvert software, part of the ProteoWizard package... The converted files were treated using the MZMine software suite v. 2.38... Eventually the resulting aligned peaklist was filtered using the peak-list rows filter option in order to keep only features associated with MS2 scans.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper clearly describes MS data preparation and validation for taxonomically informed metabolite annotation, though using MZMine and MSConvert rather than the 'tima' package claimed.",
