    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/workflow-pipeline-execution-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The massive and complex sets of spectral data generated by such platforms require computational approaches for their interpretation. Computational metabolite annotation automatically links spectral data to candidate structures via a score, which is usually established between the acquired data and experimental or theoretical spectral databases (DB).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes metabolomics annotation pipeline and validation of outputs (F1 scores, precision/recall metrics), but does not explicitly address 'input data file validation' as a distinct preliminary step. The paper focuses on validating annotation quality post-execution rather than pre-execution data integrity checks.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fpls-2019-01329",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "workflow-pipeline-execution-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Validate input data files and confirm successful execution of a complete metabolomics annotation pipeline by checking intermediate and final outputs against expected structure and content.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:19:58.538401+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/workflow-pipeline-execution-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper does not mention 'tima' or 'tima R package' anywhere. The paper describes ISDB-DNP, MS-Finder, and Sirius as the three metabolite annotation tools evaluated, but does not reference a tool called 'tima'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fpls-2019-01329",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "workflow-pipeline-execution-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "tima R package",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:19:58.538401+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/workflow-pipeline-execution-validation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The third tool to be used is Sirius 4.0. It is considered as a state-of-the-art metabolite annotation solution, which combines molecular formula calculation and the prediction of a molecular fingerprint of a query from its fragmentation tree and spectrum (D\u00fchrkop et al., 2019). Sirius uses a DB of 73,444,774 unique structures for its annotations.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses Sirius 4.0.1, not v5/v6. The version specified in the card (v5/v6) does not match the paper's actual version (4.0.1). Sirius is used as a primary annotation tool, not as 'optional external predictions'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fpls-2019-01329",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "workflow-pipeline-execution-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "SIRIUS (v5/v6 for optional external metabolite structure predictions)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:19:58.538401+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/workflow-pipeline-execution-validation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Initiatives such as the Global Natural Products Social (GNPS) molecular networking (MN) project offer both a living MS repository and the possibility to establish MN organizing MS data (Wang et al., 2016)... A feature based molecular network (https://ccms-ucsd.github.io/GNPSDocumentation/featurebasedmolecularnetworking/) was created using the .mgf file resulting from the MZMine pretreatment step... Spectral data was uploaded on the GNPS molecular networking platform.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses GNPS molecular networking (MN) and feature-based molecular networking (FBMN), but as an intermediate processing step integrated into the workflow, not as 'optional' external results. The paper describes GNPS as part of the core pipeline for Glaucium analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fpls-2019-01329",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "workflow-pipeline-execution-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "GNPS-FBMN (provides optional spectral networking results for annotation validation)",
